
# ðŸ“ Blog Generator using AWS Lambda, Amazon Bedrock, and API Gateway

> ðŸ“º **Reference Video**: [YouTube - AWS Bedrock Lambda Blog Generator](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3OP39y4dO_Y&list=PLZoTAELRMXVP5zpBfH7pab4aB1LbmCM1z&index=7)

This project automatically generates a 200-word blog on a given topic using [Amazon Bedrock](w) (specifically the `amazon.nova-lite-v1` model) and serves it via an [AWS Lambda](w) function behind an [API Gateway](w). Optionally, the generated blog can be saved to [Amazon S3](w).

---

## ðŸ”§ Architecture

* **API Gateway** â€“ Exposes a REST endpoint for blog generation.
* **AWS Lambda** â€“ Executes Python code to interact with Bedrock (runtime: `Python 3.12`, architecture: `x86_64`).
* **Amazon Bedrock** â€“ Uses `amazon.nova-lite-v1` for LLM inference (region: `eu-north-1`).
* **Amazon S3** â€“ (Optional) Used to persist the generated blogs.

